\begin_layout Standard
i) We are sorry for the confusing use of the word ignition, the manuscript
 has been revised to use terms more appropriate in this context.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
ii) We are very much aware that the particles might show structural changes
 during the oscillation cycle.
 However, the fact that the conversion rate is unchanged during very long
 timescales does lead us to belive that it not a likely scenario.
 Notice that the oscillations are reproduceble on a quite large varity of
 sizes which we belive also points againts a structual change as the primary
 oscillation mechanism.
 This does not mean that particles do not change shape during the cycle,
 more that we do not expect this to be the cause of the oscillations or
 the increasing oscillation period.
 The manuscript has been revised to make this point more clear.
\end_layout

