vi) We are ourselves vey much in doubt whether the reaction is iso-thermal
 on a microscopic level .
 On one hand the free energy pr.
 reaction is quite large and possibly distriuted on a rather small amount
 of nanoparticles.
 On the other hand heat transport in a small volume at 1bar should be very
 efficient.
 As mentioned in the paper, we have done several attempts at observing a
 possible sign local temperature effects, so far without results.
 Thus one so far has to conclude that the experimental results points towards
 constant temperature also at the microscopic level, but we are not confident
 enough in this yet to draw solid conclusions.
\end_layout

